The way people use "human" today almost always means "too human"

If to be "human" means to lack dignity, one would be better off to do as Abba John the Dwarf who left his cloak in his cell and went out into the desert saying from now on he will live as an angel who does not eat or drink.

The bitter lesson (in here) is that if one is ever genuinely humiliated, maybe by some boss or professor or workplace enemy (if such exists), it is better to just leave and never return than to remain and suffer continued humiliation. Just go to a different place. Somewhere else.
